<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - THERMOSTAT AND COOLANT FILTER -
        Thermostat - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <figure id="f1200807" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3330.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Thermostat and Outlet Tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant Outlet Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thermostat</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Thermostat Gasket (Square Cross Section)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the thermostat into the water pump housing. Make sure the arrow on the thermostat is
                pointing toward the rear of the engine or toward the rear flange bolt.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the thermostat gasket over the thermostat. Make sure the gasket is completely
                seated.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the coolant outlet tube on the water pump housing. To ensure a tight fit, make sure the
                outlet tube flange is not bent or distorted.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install three mounting bolts finger tight. Then tighten the mounting bolts evenly to the
                standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
